  "doc_id": "34192",
  "text": "ILC subpopulations were gated based on surface staining. ILC3s express cKit. 21 ILC3s expressing CD56 were defined as NCR+ ILC3s (NKp46), approximately half of which express CD56, while CD56-negative ILC3s were considered to be either LTi cells or the half of NCR+ ILC3s that do not express CD56. [CITATION_1] 21 For the purposes of this paper, these cKit-positive/CD56-negative ILC3s will be referred to as CD56 neg ILC3s. ILCs that were cKit-negative were considered to be ILC1s. 21 While these might represent classical NK cells, it is increasingly thought that conventional NK cells are CD127-negative and these CD127+/CD56+ cells are NCR+ ILCs. 7 Figures 1G-H show these different subpopulations.",
